my:Hazard.my:ControlMeasures:
a) Use of suitable and appropriate PPE: overalls, safety shoes, hard hat, gloves, etc.; 
b) All crew engaged in the rigging / stowing of the accommodation ladder / gangway are to wear a safety harness connected to the fall arrest equipment and don a lifejacket; 
c) A safety net must be rigged as per IMO regulations; 
d) Adequate lighting to be provided.

a) Adequate lighting to be provided; 
b) Trip hazards to be clearly marked; 
c) All steps, platform and deck surface should be clear of any oil and / or grease residue.

a) Use of sufficient and appropriate PPE: overalls, safety shoes, hard hat, gloves, safety harness, buoyancy aid, etc.; 
b) Adequate lighting to be provided; 
c) Crew vigilance - Constant monitoring of the task; 
d) Sufficient number of crew to be made available; 
e) Any crew not directly involved in the rigging / stowing of the accommodation ladder / gangway should stay well clear; 
f) Consult 'Manual Handling' Risk Assessment, if necessary; 
g) Consult 'Crane Operation' Risk Assessment, if necessary.

a) Maintenance and inspections to be carried out in accordance with the Manufacturer's Manual and Company MPM system; 
b) The accommodation ladder, gangway, davit, winches, hooks, etc. are to be visually inspected for any defects prior to use; 
c) Plywood or planks should be placed under the accommodation ladder / gangway to prevent damage to the roller.

a) All crew should be made aware of the tidal range at the port; 
b) A copy of the tidal information should be made available at the accommodation ladder / gangway; 
c) The OOW and Watchman should monitor the affects of the tide on the accommodation ladder / gangway and adjust the accommodation ladder / gangway accordingly.
